Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with motion planning for robots in cluttered environments.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes an online re-planning approach using stochastic trajectory optimization, which involves AI techniques.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is a possibility as visual perception is often used in grasping tasks, although it is not explicitly mentioned in the abstract.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possibility as the stochastic trajectory optimization algorithm may involve machine learning techniques.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possibility as the paper deals with controlling a multi-body multi-contact physical system.
